. Leptin is secreted by white adipose tissue as a negative feedback response to maintain body weight by regulating appetite and fat metabolism (1). Leptin receptors (ObRs) are present in the brain (the choroid plexus and hypothalamus) and many peripheral tissues, such as the lungs, kidneys, adrenals, and lymph nodes (2, 3). There are at least six types of ObRs (a, b, c, d, e, and f). Administration of leptin is able to correct obesity in humans and in 